WEBVTT

00:00:00.001 --> 00:00:02.600
Next on PIJN News,

00:00:02.600 --> 00:00:06.480
Dr. Chaps reports on these important issues.

00:00:06.480 --> 00:00:09.720
A pastor testifies before the Department of Justice

00:00:09.720 --> 00:00:13.420
how the IRS targeted his church.

00:00:13.420 --> 00:00:15.920
Colonel Glenn Holloway has written an important book

00:00:15.920 --> 00:00:18.040
about farming God's way

00:00:18.040 --> 00:00:20.740
and putting nutrition back into your food supply.

00:00:20.740 --> 00:00:24.920
Former Navy Chaplain, Gordon James Klingenschmitt

00:00:24.920 --> 00:00:26.960
took a stand to defend religious freedom

00:00:26.960 --> 00:00:29.840
by daring to pray publicly in Jesus' name.

00:00:29.840 --> 00:00:32.160
Now he helps you by reporting the news,

00:00:32.160 --> 00:00:34.960
discerning the spirits and praying the scriptures.

00:00:34.960 --> 00:00:36.060
Would you pray with us?

00:00:36.060 --> 00:00:37.380
Here's Dr. Chaps.

00:00:37.380 --> 00:00:43.060
God bless you in Jesus' name.

00:00:43.060 --> 00:00:46.480
My name is Chaplain Gordon James Klingenschmitt, Dr. Chaps,

00:00:46.480 --> 00:00:48.880
and you're watching PIJN News.

00:00:48.880 --> 00:00:50.780
On this show, we'd like to do three things.

00:00:50.780 --> 00:00:53.160
We report the news, we discern the spirits,

00:00:53.160 --> 00:00:56.120
and we pray the scriptures in Jesus' name.

00:00:56.120 --> 00:00:58.680
Are you ready to pray the news with us?

00:00:58.680 --> 00:00:59.840
Here's our first story.

00:00:59.840 --> 00:01:03.960
A famous pastor has now testified

00:01:03.960 --> 00:01:05.880
before the Department of Justice

00:01:05.880 --> 00:01:09.300
that the IRS targeted his church.

00:01:09.300 --> 00:01:11.880
Christian Post reports,

00:01:11.880 --> 00:01:16.880
"First Baptist Dallas pastor warns that the IRS overreach

00:01:16.880 --> 00:01:19.060
"in linking biblical beliefs

00:01:19.060 --> 00:01:21.600
"with prohibited political speech.

00:01:21.600 --> 00:01:26.660
"Pastor Robert Jeffress of First Baptist Church

00:01:26.660 --> 00:01:29.780
"says that it's none of the government's business

00:01:29.780 --> 00:01:33.880
"for the IRS to regulate the content of his sermons

00:01:33.880 --> 00:01:36.320
"that pastors preach from the pulpit."

00:01:36.320 --> 00:01:41.460
He told a White House Religious Liberty panel on

00:01:41.460 --> 00:01:42.620
Wednesday

00:01:42.620 --> 00:01:45.600
in his testimony before the US Department of Justice

00:01:45.600 --> 00:01:47.640
and their Religious Liberty Commission.

00:01:47.640 --> 00:01:52.220
Pastor Jeffress and First Baptist Dallas

00:01:52.220 --> 00:01:57.220
senior executive pastor, Ben Loeworn,

00:01:57.220 --> 00:01:59.200
shared their experience with the IRS

00:01:59.200 --> 00:02:04.200
during a controversial church tax inquiry in 2021,

00:02:04.200 --> 00:02:07.200
which was initiated under the regime

00:02:07.200 --> 00:02:09.440
of former President Joe Biden.

00:02:09.440 --> 00:02:13.520
Robert Jeffress' statement to the commission,

00:02:13.520 --> 00:02:15.960
including comments which he initially shared

00:02:15.960 --> 00:02:18.140
with his congregation on Sunday,

00:02:18.140 --> 00:02:21.680
in which he recounted how the atheist organization,

00:02:21.680 --> 00:02:24.040
Freedom From Religion Foundation,

00:02:24.040 --> 00:02:26.940
had filed a complaint with the IRS

00:02:26.940 --> 00:02:31.940
after then Vice President Mike Pence

00:02:31.940 --> 00:02:37.320
and then Secretary of HUD, Dr. Ben Carson,

00:02:37.320 --> 00:02:40.500
had come to First Baptist Dallas

00:02:40.500 --> 00:02:42.280
and had shared their faith testimonies

00:02:42.280 --> 00:02:45.400
of how they came to know Jesus Christ as Savior.

00:02:45.400 --> 00:02:48.520
They visited the church

00:02:48.520 --> 00:02:51.520
as many Democrats visit Democrat churches.

00:02:51.520 --> 00:02:54.920
These Republicans visited a conservative church

00:02:54.920 --> 00:02:59.240
in June of 2020 and they spoke to the congregation.

00:02:59.240 --> 00:03:01.000
Well, that upset the atheists.

00:03:01.000 --> 00:03:06.680
So Pastor Jeffress told the panel what happened next.

00:03:06.680 --> 00:03:10.120
He said, quote, "It's interesting that we did not hear

00:03:10.120 --> 00:03:13.320
"anything from the IRS for 11 months."

00:03:13.320 --> 00:03:16.620
And four months after Joe Biden became president,

00:03:16.620 --> 00:03:21.470
it was on May 6th of 2021 that the IRS informed our

00:03:21.470 --> 00:03:21.620
church

00:03:21.620 --> 00:03:24.700
that they were initiating an inquiry

00:03:24.700 --> 00:03:27.940
into the tax exempt status of our church

00:03:27.940 --> 00:03:32.180
because we held a patriotic service, end quote.

00:03:32.180 --> 00:03:36.760
Noting that First Baptist Dallas had never had any

00:03:36.760 --> 00:03:37.160
issue

00:03:37.160 --> 00:03:41.420
with the IRS prior to Joe Biden being elected,

00:03:41.420 --> 00:03:43.960
Jeffress said he has a history now of encouraging

00:03:43.960 --> 00:03:44.380
pastors

00:03:44.380 --> 00:03:47.280
to follow IRS regulations.

00:03:47.280 --> 00:03:50.480
In fact, he does not and encourages others

00:03:50.480 --> 00:03:53.540
not to endorse any candidates from the pulpit.

00:03:53.540 --> 00:03:56.740
And in his testimony, Pastor Jeffress pointed out

00:03:56.740 --> 00:04:00.400
that back in November of 2020,

00:04:00.400 --> 00:04:02.960
the same day he was talking to his church

00:04:02.960 --> 00:04:04.440
about the presidential race,

00:04:04.440 --> 00:04:10.160
Joe Biden himself was campaigning at a church

00:04:10.160 --> 00:04:13.000
and spoke at the Sharon Baptist Church in Philadelphia.

00:04:13.100 --> 00:04:18.100
Jeffress pointed out that the former President Biden

00:04:18.100 --> 00:04:21.760
and that pastor had openly encouraged members

00:04:21.760 --> 00:04:23.080
to vote for Biden.

00:04:23.080 --> 00:04:26.610
Well, both men were standing in front of the campaign

00:04:26.610 --> 00:04:27.060
banner

00:04:27.060 --> 00:04:29.540
at the front of that church in Philadelphia.

00:04:29.540 --> 00:04:31.880
So the Democrats can get away with it,

00:04:31.880 --> 00:04:33.060
but the Republicans can't

00:04:33.060 --> 00:04:35.060
when they don't even endorse candidates.

00:04:35.060 --> 00:04:38.320
Esther Jeffress added the following, quote,

00:04:38.320 --> 00:04:40.400
"When we pointed out the contrast to the IRS

00:04:40.400 --> 00:04:42.620
"between our non-endorsement policy

00:04:42.620 --> 00:04:46.200
"and this church's flagrant disregard

00:04:46.200 --> 00:04:47.540
"for the Johnson Amendment,

00:04:47.540 --> 00:04:51.520
"the IRS officials conducting the examination

00:04:51.520 --> 00:04:54.340
"had no response," end quote.

00:04:54.340 --> 00:04:59.640
Well, that inquiry lasted more than a year,

00:04:59.640 --> 00:05:02.280
like an audit of a church.

00:05:02.280 --> 00:05:03.120
Who does that?

00:05:03.120 --> 00:05:06.600
The IRS eventually acknowledged a year later in 2020,

00:05:06.600 --> 00:05:10.500
July 2022, that the first Baptist Dallas,

00:05:10.500 --> 00:05:13.860
in fact, did not engage in any improper

00:05:13.860 --> 00:05:16.620
political interventions or violate the US tax code.

00:05:16.620 --> 00:05:18.700
That's the news.

00:05:18.700 --> 00:05:21.560
Our thanks to Christian Post for that report.

00:05:21.560 --> 00:05:24.700
You may be surprised to learn

00:05:24.700 --> 00:05:27.040
that our ministry underwent the same thing.

00:05:27.040 --> 00:05:32.300
In 2022, I believe it was,

00:05:32.300 --> 00:05:35.540
the IRS showed up at our door.

00:05:35.540 --> 00:05:38.000
I don't have a church, but I have a religious nonprofit,

00:05:38.000 --> 00:05:40.460
25 years old now, never had a problem,

00:05:40.460 --> 00:05:45.220
always did our 990s, always filed, tracked every penny.

00:05:45.220 --> 00:05:47.140
But when the IRS shows up and does an audit

00:05:47.140 --> 00:05:49.140
of our organization, as they did,

00:05:49.140 --> 00:05:52.180
he spent two years in our offices.

00:05:52.180 --> 00:05:57.980
Like all of 2022, '23, he was in our offices

00:05:57.980 --> 00:06:02.900
and at his own office, looking through every one

00:06:02.900 --> 00:06:06.260
of our tax year filings from 2019 to 2020,

00:06:06.260 --> 00:06:10.660
found nothing wrong, except two things.

00:06:10.660 --> 00:06:14.740
You didn't properly report the mileage on a company car.

00:06:14.740 --> 00:06:16.020
Okay, no problem.

00:06:16.020 --> 00:06:21.300
But then, the content of your sermon

00:06:21.300 --> 00:06:24.220
on your television show, we noticed that you prayed

00:06:24.220 --> 00:06:26.580
for one of the candidates in Jesus' name.

00:06:26.580 --> 00:06:28.900
Was your prayer to God an implied endorsement

00:06:28.900 --> 00:06:30.000
of his candidacy?

00:06:30.000 --> 00:06:35.260
Gave us a slap on the wrist and we passed the audit.

00:06:36.260 --> 00:06:40.040
On the condition that we never do that again.

00:06:40.040 --> 00:06:42.300
Don't pray for candidates.

00:06:42.300 --> 00:06:43.580
Really?

00:06:43.580 --> 00:06:45.140
The US government is going to intervene

00:06:45.140 --> 00:06:46.800
in my prayers to God?

00:06:46.800 --> 00:06:50.780
This would be the third time in my lifetime

00:06:50.780 --> 00:06:53.820
that I would end up in court over the content

00:06:53.820 --> 00:06:55.380
of my prayers to God.

00:06:55.380 --> 00:06:59.220
The Bible says this in Matthew 22.

00:06:59.220 --> 00:07:01.180
He said to them, render therefore unto Caesar

00:07:01.180 --> 00:07:02.200
the things that are Caesar,

00:07:02.200 --> 00:07:04.120
and to God the things that are God's.

00:07:04.120 --> 00:07:07.680
We should pay our taxes.

00:07:07.680 --> 00:07:10.220
But if the money belongs to God,

00:07:10.220 --> 00:07:11.720
we should not give that to the government,

00:07:11.720 --> 00:07:13.420
we should give that to God's work.

00:07:13.420 --> 00:07:16.760
Nonprofits are sacred and so are churches.

00:07:16.760 --> 00:07:20.100
IRS, stay out of our preaching and out of our pulpits.

